  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dac\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dda\u0db1\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0db8\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A committee to investigate about Dadulena",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Will the chipmunk be delisted from national animal status? no? Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Conservation Minister Mahinda Amaraweera says that a committee was appointed to decide.",
        "The committee includes the Secretary of the Ministry of Agriculture and the Secretary of the Ministry of Wildlife.",
        "The minister stated that the decision of the committee will be acted upon as well as the opinions and suggestions of the public and if they wish to keep the Ddulena as the national animal, there is no objection.",
        "Agriculture Minister Mahinda Amaraweera also said that arbitrary decisions will never be taken regarding the removal of the Dadulena from the national animal status.",
        "Although the Ministry of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation had previously decided to include the Dadulena in the list of animals that cause crop damage, a problematic situation arose due to the fact that the Dadulena was named as the national animal of Sri Lanka."
      ],
